description.narrative: By 2022, the MOH and public health centre have enhanced capacity to generate evidence-based data, develop policy and strategy and design service delivery models for maternal and child health in the context of the health reform., which contributes to Adolescent Health And Nutrition, Child Health, Child Health (Covid), Immunization, Maternal And Newborn Health, Prevention Of Stunting And Other Forms Of Malnutrition. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Advocacy And Public Engagement, Developing And Leveraging Resources And Partnerships, Evaluations, Research And Data, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: By 2022, all children and pregnant women in Ukraine, including in situations of humanitarian crisis, utilize improved quality and affordable mother and child health-care services.
